ðŸ§­ Foundational Exams
These are the primary certifications for administrators and developers working with OpenShift.

Red Hat Certified OpenShift Administrator exam (EX280) This exam tests the skills required to create, configure, and manage a cloud application platform using Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform.

Red Hat Certified OpenShift Application Developer exam (EX288) This exam focuses on the skills needed to build and deploy containerized applications on an OpenShift cluster.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in Containers (EX188) While not exclusively an OpenShift exam, this certification validates the foundational skills for working with containers using Podman, which is a core technology for OpenShift.

ðŸš€ Specialist Exams
These exams allow professionals to validate deeper, specialized skills in specific areas of the OpenShift ecosystem.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in OpenShift Virtualization (EX316) Tests the ability to create and manage virtual machines using the OpenShift Virtualization feature.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in Building Resilient Microservices (EX328) Focuses on skills for developing and implementing resilient microservices using Istio and Red Hat OpenShift Service Mesh.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in OpenShift Data Foundation (EX370) Validates skills for deploying and managing Red Hat OpenShift Data Foundation (formerly OpenShift Container Storage) to provide persistent storage for applications.

Red Hat Certified Cloud-Native Developer (EX378) Tests the skills to develop, test, and deploy applications using Quarkus on Red Hat OpenShift.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in OpenShift Automation and Integration (EX380) Validates skills in managing and automating OpenShift clusters at scale, including integration with other enterprise systems.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in OpenShift Advanced Cluster Security (EX430) Tests the ability to secure OpenShift clusters and applications using Red Hat Advanced Cluster Security for Kubernetes (RHACS).

Red Hat Certified Specialist in OpenShift Advanced Cluster Management (EX432) Focuses on the skills needed to manage and control multiple OpenShift clusters from a single point using Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in MultiCluster Management (EX480) Validates the skills for using Red Hat Advanced Cluster Management for Kubernetes to manage multiple clusters.

Red Hat Certified Specialist in Event-Driven Application Development (EX482) Tests the ability to design and develop event-driven applications using Apache Kafka and Red Hat AMQ Streams.